<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" dir="ltr">

<head>
  <%- include('../head') %>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Product Registration</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/CSS/iot.css" />
</head>

<body>
  <div id="iot_content">
    <%- include('nav') %>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="container mb-3">
          <h2>How to use AUTOINIoT</h2>
        </div>
        <div id="help" class="container">
          <ul id="help-list" class="list-feature">
            <li>
              <a data-toggle="collapse" class="collapsed" href="#help1">Regist Item <i
                  class="ion-android-remove"></i></a>
              <div id="help1" class="collapse" data-parent="#help-list">
                <p>After attaching the RFID label, input the tag name, select the logistics name and quantity of
                  goods.<br>
                  When the goods are received, the stock status changes to 'received complete', and you can check the
                  photos of the stocked goods.<br>
                  Click the Register button to register the product, and click the Cancel button to cancel the product
                  registration.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a data-toggle="collapse" class="collapsed" href="#help2">Edit Item <i class="ion-android-remove"></i></a>
              <div id="help2" class="collapse" data-parent="#help-list">
                <p>It is possible to edit the registered goods, and by using the "Edit" button on the right side of the
                  registered goods,<br>
                  you can edit the product information. RFID is immutable and the name and quantity can be changed.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#help3" class="collapsed">Check warehouse status - temperature/humidity <i
                  class="ion-android-remove"></i></a>
              <div id="help3" class="collapse" data-parent="#help-list">
                <p>It displays the temperature/humidity recognized by the sensor in the current warehouse in real
                  time.<br>
                  When the threshold value set by the user is exceeded, an alarm is generated.</p>
                <img src="Public/Image/iot_help1.PNG" alt="help1">
              </div>
            </li>

            <li>
              <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#help4" class="collapsed">Check Warehouse Status - Flame/Gas <i
                  class="ion-android-remove"></i></a>
              <div id="help4" class="collapse" data-parent="#help-list">
                <p>It indicates in real time whether a fire/smoke has occurred in the current warehouse.<br>
                  When a flame or smoke is detected, it turns red and an alarm is generated.</p>
                <img src="Public/Image/iot_help2.PNG" alt="help2">
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
  </div>
</body>
<%- include('../footer') %>

</html>